@@ -0,0 +1,81 @@
+# Gated-DeltaNet (GDN) tuning — gfx1151 / Qwythos
+
+Optimizations for Qwen3.5 linear-attention layers on AMD RDNA3.5 (`gfx1151`, Strix Halo / 8060S).
+
+## Track A: GDN kernel occupancy (`gated_delta_net.cu`)
+
+### Baseline (pre-tuning)
+
+| Parameter | Value |
+|-----------|-------|
+| Grid | `(H, n_seqs, ⌈S_v / 4⌉)` |
+| Block | `(warp_size, 4, 1)` → 128 threads for S_v=128 |
+| Token loop | Serial `for (t = 0; t < n_tokens; t++)` inside each block |
+| `__launch_bounds__` | `(128, 2)` |
+
+For Qwythos (32 heads, S_v=128, decode): **1024 blocks × 128 threads**, 4 columns per block.
+
+### RDNA3.5 tuning (gfx1151)
+
+Runtime CC check: `GGML_CUDA_CC_IS_RDNA3_5` (`common.cuh`).
+
+| Mode | Condition | Warps/block | Grid Z | Threads | `launch_bounds` min blocks |
+|------|-----------|-------------|--------|---------|----------------------------|
+| **Decode** | `S_v==128`, `n_tokens==1` | **8** | **16** | 256 | 1 |
+| **Prefill** | `S_v==128`, `n_tokens>1` | 4 | 32 | 128 | 1 |
+| **Default** | other CC / S_v | 4 | ⌈S_v/4⌉ | 128 | 2 |
+
+**Rationale:** Decode is register-light (one token iteration) but launches many small blocks (one per head × 32 column-tiles). Doubling warps/block halves grid-Z launches and improves wave occupancy on gfx1151 without changing numerics. Prefill keeps 4 warps (heavier serial token loop) but relaxes `min blocks/SM` from 2→1 on RDNA3.5 to reduce register pressure spill.
+
+### Override / debug
+
+No env var yet. To experiment, edit `gdn_pick_num_warps()` in `ggml/src/ggml-cuda/gated_delta_net.cu`.
+
+## Track B: Pre-GDN micro-fusion
+
+### B1 — q/k L2-norm fused into GDN
+
+**Graph change** (`src/models/qwen35.cpp`):
+
+When `fused_gdn_ar || fused_gdn_ch`, skip separate `ggml_l2_norm` on `q_conv` / `k_conv` and pass `eps` into `build_recurrent_attn` → `ggml_gated_delta_net(..., fuse_l2_eps)`.
+
+**Kernel** (`gated_delta_net.cu`):
+
+Per token, after loading `q_reg` / `k_reg`, warp-local L2 normalize (matches `ggml_l2_norm` / PyTorch `normalize` with `rsqrt(max(sum_sq, eps²))`).
+
+**Op param:** `op_params[1]` = `fuse_l2_eps` (float, 0 = disabled). `op_params[0]` remains snapshot count `K`.
+
+### B2 — ssm_conv + silu (existing)
+
+Already fused in `ggml-cuda.cu` for `SSM_CONV → SILU` and `SSM_CONV → ADD → SILU`.
+
+Conv-state `cpy` after `build_conv_state` is unchanged (future: optional writeback from ssm_conv tail).
+
+## Correctness tests
+
+```bash
+# HIP backend, GDN op tests only
+./build-rocm/bin/test-backend-ops test -b ROCm0 -o GATED_DELTA_NET
+```
+
+Reference tests still apply external `ggml_l2_norm` with `fuse_l2_eps=0`.
+
+## Benchmark (mandatory lock)
+
+**Only** use the flock-wrapped script — one GPU benchmark at a time:
+
+```bash
+/home/ai/projects/llamacpp-qwen35-rocm/scripts/bench-pp-tps.sh \
+  --url http://127.0.0.1:50127 --title gdn-tuned
+```
+
+## Build
+
+```bash
+cd llama.cpp
+ROCM_PATH=/opt/rocm-7.2.3 cmake -B build-rocm -DGGML_HIP=ON -DAMDGPU_TARGETS=gfx1151 \
+  -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DLLAMA_BUILD_TESTS=ON
+cmake --build build-rocm --target ggml-hip -j$(nproc)
+```
+
+**Status (2026-07-12):** `libggml-hip.so` builds cleanly with GDN changes for `gfx1151`. Chunked prefill kernels are compile-disabled on RDNA3.5 (`GGML_CUDA_GDN_CHUNKED=0`) because `gdn_chunk_output_kernel<64,128>` exceeds the 64 KiB LDS limit; prefill uses the serial token-loop kernel with occupancy tuning above. Full `llama-server` / `test-backend-ops` link currently blocked by unrelated `common/speculative.cpp` fork WIP.
diff --git a/docs/MTP_GPU_RESIDENT.md b/docs/MTP_GPU_RESIDENT.md
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..e8477437
--- /dev/null
+++ b/docs/MTP_GPU_RESIDENT.md
@@ -0,0 +1,111 @@
+# GPU-resident MTP draft path
+
+Reduces `synchronize()` + device-to-host (D2H) traffic in the draft-MTP hot loop by keeping `h_nextn` (pre-output-norm hidden states) on the GPU between target verification and draft-head decodes.
+
+## Problem
+
+Classic draft-MTP (`common/speculative.cpp`) did per-step:
+
+1. Target decode → D2H all `h_nextn` rows into host `embd_nextn`
+2. `memcpy` into `batch.embd` → H2D on draft `llama_decode`
+3. Draft loop: after each draft token, `llama_get_embeddings_nextn_ith()` → **full graph sync + D2H** for one row
+
+Each `llama_get_embeddings_nextn_ith()` call synchronizes the whole context (`llama-context.cpp`), which is expensive on ROCm when repeated for every draft step.
+
+## Approach
+
+### 1. Device staging buffer (`llama-context.cpp`)
+
+When `embeddings_nextn_gpu_resident` is enabled:
+
+- Allocate `t_embd_nextn_dev` on the model output device (mirrors host `embd_nextn` layout).
+- `handle_mtp_for_ubatch()` — called at the end of each decode ubatch — copies `t_h_nextn` → `t_embd_nextn_dev` with `ggml_backend_tensor_copy` (D2D), **skipping bulk D2H**.
+- Host `embd_nextn` is still allocated for logits/sampling APIs; single-row reads use lazy D2H via `llama_mtp_get_h_row()`.
+
+### 2. Queued inp-h copies (`apply_mtp_h_pending`)
+
+MTP graphs use `llm_graph_input_embd_h` (`inp->h`). Before decode:
+
+- `llama_mtp_queue_h_rows(ctx_dst, ctx_src, dst_row, src_row, n_rows)` records D2D row copies.
+- After `set_inputs()`, `apply_mtp_h_pending()` copies from src staging into `t_inp_h` on the device.
+
+This replaces host `batch.embd` ↔ GPU ping-pong for hidden rows in the draft loop.
+
+### 3. Speculative driver (`common/speculative.cpp`)
+
+Auto-enabled when `draft.n_gpu_layers > 0`:
+
+| Phase | Host path (before) | GPU-resident path |
+|-------|-------------------|-------------------|
+| `process()` catch-up shift | D2H all tgt rows + memcpy | D2D tgt→dft rows `1..n-1` ← `0..n-2` |
+| `process()` pending row | memcpy | one small H2D (carryover from prior batch) |
+| `process()` verify stash | D2H all rows into `verify_h` | store row index only; D2H last row for pending |
+| `draft()` loop | sync+D2H per step | D2D dft row `0` → new inp row |
+| `accept()` | memcpy from `verify_h` | single-row D2H from tgt staging |
+
+`chain_heads` (Step-3.5 multi-head) still uses the host path.
+
+### 4. GDN keep-intermediates (`delta-net-base.cpp`)
+
+When `n_rs_seq > 0`, the expensive snapshot-keeping GDN path is only used for **multi-token** ubatches (`n_seq_tokens > 1`), e.g. speculative verification. Single-token MTP draft steps use the cheaper AR kernel even if rollback is enabled on the target context.
+
+## API (`src/llama-ext.h`)
+
+```c
+void llama_set_embeddings_nextn_gpu_resident(llama_context * ctx, bool value);
+void llama_mtp_clear_h_pending(llama_context * ctx_dst);
+void llama_mtp_queue_h_rows(llama_context * ctx_dst, llama_context * ctx_src,
+                            int32_t dst_row, int32_t src_row, int32_t n_rows);
+bool llama_mtp_get_h_row(llama_context * ctx, int32_t row, float * dst, int32_t n_embd);
+```
+
+## Build (ROCm / gfx1151)
+
+```bash
+cd llama.cpp
+cmake -B build-rocm -DGGML_HIP=on -DAMDGPU_TARGETS=gfx1151 \
+  -DLLAMA_BUILD_SERVER=ON -DLLAMA_BUILD_UI=OFF \
+  -DCMAKE_HIP_FLAGS="-DRDNA3_5"
+cmake --build build-rocm -j$(nproc)
+```
+
+`-DRDNA3_5` disables chunked GDN kernels that exceed 64 KiB LDS on gfx1151 (see `docs/GDN_TUNING.md`).
+
+CPU-only syntax check: `cmake -B build-cpu -DGGML_HIP=OFF && cmake --build build-cpu --target llama-server`.
+
+## Benchmark (profile lock required)
+
+Stop competing GPU containers, run host server on port 50128, then:
+
+```bash
+docker stop prompt-router-llamacpp-rocm-qwythos-9b-v2-mtp-q8  # bench only
+
+export HSA_OVERRIDE_GFX_VERSION=11.5.1
+export LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$PWD/build-rocm/bin:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH
+./build-rocm/bin/llama-server --host 127.0.0.1 --port 50128 \
+  -m /path/to/Qwythos-9B-v2-MTP-Q8_0.gguf \
+  --n-gpu-layers 99 --ctx-size 16384 --batch-size 2048 --ubatch-size 256 \
+  --jinja --spec-type draft-mtp --spec-draft-n-max 6 --parallel 1
+
+/home/ai/projects/llamacpp-qwen35-rocm/scripts/bench-pp-tps.sh \
+  --url http://127.0.0.1:50128 --title mtp-gpu-resident --runs 3
+```
+
+### Result (2026-07-12, this branch)
+
+| Metric | Value |
+|--------|-------|
+| PP mean | 126.5 tok/s |
+| Decode mean | 20.2 tok/s |
+| Draft accept | ~240 drafts / ~87 accepted (~36%) |
+
+Reference upstream baseline on same machine (`var/profiles/upstream_baseline.json`): decode ~21–26 tok/s. Further tuning (async D2D, same-stream copies, batching pending queues) may be needed to realize the expected win; correctness path is in place.
+
+## Files touched
+
+- `src/llama-cparams.h` — `embeddings_nextn_gpu_resident`
+- `src/llama-context.{h,cpp}` — staging, `handle_mtp_for_ubatch`, MTP queue API
+- `src/llama-ext.h` — public staging helpers
+- `src/llama-graph.{h,cpp}` — track `t_inp_h` for MTP inp
+- `src/models/delta-net-base.cpp` — GDN keep guard
+- `common/speculative.cpp` — GPU-resident draft-MTP driver
